Create a gt table object

Source: R/gt.R
gt.Rd

Create a gt table object so that we can perform styling transformations before transforming the entire object to a display table. Using this function is the first step in that process, and, there are a few data ingest options we can consider at this stage.

gt(data, rownames_to_stub = FALSE)

Arguments

data

a data.frame object or a tibble.
rownames_to_stub

an option to take rownames from the input data table as row captions in the stub.

Value

an object of class gt_tbl.

See also

Other table-part creation/modification functions: gt_preview, tab_boxhead_panel, tab_footnote, tab_heading, tab_options, tab_source_note, tab_stub_block, tab_stubhead_caption, tab_style

Examples

# Create a table object using the
# `mtcars` dataset
tab <-
  gt(mtcars, rownames_to_stub = TRUE)

# The resulting object can be used
# in transformations
tab_2 <-
  tab %>%
  fmt_number(
    columns = vars(drat, wt, qsec),
    decimals = 1)

# The object of this type can be
# displayed in the Viewer
tab_2
